    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>BRITISH INSURANCE DEAL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Suzanne Kapner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Kapner, Suzanne</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Royal London Mutual Insurance Society will buy Scottish Life Assurance Co for 1.1 billion pounds ($1.63 billion) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A big British insurer, the Royal London Mutual Insurance Society, will buy the Scottish Life Assurance Company for $:1.1 billion ($1.63 billion) in the latest in a string of British insurance company mergers. In winning Scottish Life, Royal London, which will gain access to new distribution channels, including important independent brokers, beat out several other suitors, including GE Capital. The combined entity will have income of $:1.9 billion ($2.81 billion) and manage funds worth nearly $:30 billion ($44.31 billion).</p>
        <p>Suzanne Kapner</p>
      </block>
